		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Trius&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Well written for group strategy, but don't let this post scare yo away fro the bard, we can solo and solo very well.&nbsp;&nbsp;To solo as a bard requires some work and imagination as they do not solo intuitively.  We are not tanks.  The bard is a caster, think of the bard this way and it may break your concept of how you should battle.  I have seen countless bards tricked by the lull of duel wield sluggung and bellowing it out toe to toe with enemies, even I used to think that this way the efficient way to fight.  The truth is that the bard does not have enough hitpoints to do this. You lack the mighty double attack of the tank classes as well.  Bards can kite well, especially if they have SOW so they do not need to twist selos.  Bards hets good DOTs, lulls, charms, fears and roots.  These can be cast without mana on the move with no line of sight.  The bard is an amazing caster, but a mediacre tank.  Work hard and play your character smart, you will see what I mean. =)<br><br>Trius Deme<br>One Hundred Swords  </p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Master of Mischief</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=4><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=4&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" 